Dragonfly Doji

    Definition: A bullish reversal pattern with open and close near the high, a long lower shadow, and no upper shadow.
    Criteria:
        Body: abs(close - open) ≤ 5% of range.
        Lower shadow: min(open, close) - low ≥ 70% of range.
        Upper shadow: high - max(open, close) ≤ 5% of range.
    What It Tells a Trader:
        Bullish Reversal: Sellers pushed prices down, but buyers closed near the high, showing strong buying support.
        Context-Dependent: Effective at support after a downtrend.
    How to Trade It:
        Entry: Long at the close or on bullish confirmation (e.g., breakout above the Doji’s high).
        Stop-Loss: Below the Doji’s low (1-2x atr14).
        Take-Profit: Next resistance (2-3x risk).
        Confirmation: RSI 30-50, ADX < 25, high volume_surge_ratio, order_book_imbalance > 0.5.
        Futures Notes: Low leverage, stops below low, check bid_ask_spread.